 tries browser OAuth (FAILS)\\n- `AMAZON_Q_SIGV4=1 kiro-cli-chat chat --no-interactive \\\"hello\\\"` → uses SIGV4, works perfectly\\n\\nThis matches the `setup-kiro-action` which explicitly installs and uses `kiro-cli-chat`, not `kiro-cli`.\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. `e2e/agents/kiro.go` — Switch binary name\\n\\n- `Binary()` → return `\\\"kiro-cli-chat\\\"` instead of `\\\"kiro-cli\\\"`\\n- `init()` LookPath → check for `\\\"kiro-cli-chat\\\"`\\n- `Bootstrap()` whoami command → use `\\\"kiro-cli-chat\\\"`\\n- Update comments referencing `kiro-cli`\\n\\n### 2. `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` — Fix install command\\n\\nLine 73: Replace `curl -fsSL https://cli.kiro.dev/install | bash` with direct binary download (matching setup-kiro-action pattern):\\n```bash\\nkiro)\\n  KIRO_VERSION=\\\"1.27.0\\\"\\n  curl -fsSL \\\"https://desktop-release.q.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/${KIRO_VERSION}/kirocli-x86_64-linux.zip\\\" -o kiro.zip\\n  unzip -q kiro.zip\\n  cp kirocli/bin/kiro-cli-chat ~/.local/bin/\\n  chmod +x ~/.local/bin/kiro-cli-chat\\n  rm -rf kirocli kiro.zip\\n  ;;\\n```\\n\\n### 3. `.github/workflows/e2e-isolated.yml` — Same install fix\\n\\nLine 45: Same binary download change as above.\\n\\n### 4. `e2e/README.md` — Update Kiro auth docs\\n\\n- Update binary name references\\n- Note that `kiro-cli-chat` (not `kiro-cli`) is required for SIGV4 auth\\n- Update local dev instructions (local users with desktop app can symlink or install separately)\\n\\n## Prerequisites\\n\\n- Infra PR #114 must be merged and applied (creates the IAM role)\\n- `AWS_ROLE_ARN` secret must be set in `entireio/cli` repo settings\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. **Local**: `AMAZON_Q_SIGV4=1 AWS_REGION=us-east-1 AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=<real> AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=<real> kiro-cli-chat chat --no-interactive --agent entire \\\"say hello\\\"` should work\\n2. **CI**: Run isolated E2E test: `e2e-isolated` workflow with agent=kiro, test=TestAttributionOnAgentCommit\\n3. **Unit tests**: `mise run test` (no changes to unit tests needed — this is a config/binary change)\\n\\n## Local dev note\\n\\nDevelopers who have the Kiro desktop app installed get `kiro-cli` (symlink to the app). They need `kiro-cli-chat` separately. The `curl -fsSL https://cli.kiro.dev/install | bash` script may install both — need to verify. If not, local kiro E2E testing requires the direct binary download.\\n\\n\\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/alisha/.claude/projects/-Users-alisha-Projects-wt-kiro-oneshot/39e34ee5-c069-499f-9164-8e72b34e6739.jsonl\"},\"uuid\":\"d6c8ad70-525c-410b-ba0b-ce08d8dc80ed\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T20:11:25.577Z\",\"planContent\":\"# Fix: Kiro E2E Auth — Use `kiro-cli-chat` binary\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nKiro E2E tests fail immediately (0.5s) with `OAuth error: Failed to open browser`. The root cause is that our CI uses `kiro-cli` (the desktop app wrapper) which ignores `AMAZON_Q_SIGV4` env var and always forces browser OAuth. The standalone `kiro-cli-chat` binary is the one that supports headless SIGV4 auth.\\n\\n**Verified locally:**\\n- `AMAZON_Q_SIGV4=1 kiro-cli chat --no-interactive \\\"hello\\\"` → tries browser OAuth (FAILS)\\n- `AMAZON_Q_SIGV4=1 kiro-cli-chat chat --no-interactive \\\"hello\\\"` → uses SIGV4, works perfectly\\n\\nThis matches the `setup-kiro-action` which explicitly installs and uses `kiro-cli-chat`, not `kiro-cli`.\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. `e2e/agents/kiro.go` — Switch binary name\\n\\n- `Binary()` → return `\\\"kiro-cli-chat\\\"` instead of `\\\"kiro-cli\\\"`\\n- `init()` LookPath → check for `\\\"kiro-cli-chat\\\"`\\n- `Bootstrap()` whoami command → use `\\\"kiro-cli-chat\\\"`\\n- Update comments referencing `kiro-cli`\\n\\n### 2. `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` — Fix install command\\n\\nLine 73: Replace `curl -fsSL https://cli.kiro.dev/install | bash` with direct binary download (matching setup-kiro-action pattern):\\n```bash\\nkiro)\\n  KIRO_VERSION=\\\"1.27.0\\\"\\n  curl -fsSL \\\"https://desktop-release.q.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/${KIRO_VERSION}/kirocli-x86_64-linux.zip\\\" -o kiro.zip\\n  unzip -q kiro.zip\\n  cp kirocli/bin/kiro-cli-chat ~/.local/bin/\\n  chmod +x ~/.local/bin/kiro-cli-chat\\n  rm -rf kirocli kiro.zip\\n  ;;\\n```\\n\\n### 3. `.github/workflows/e2e-isolated.yml` — Same install fix\\n\\nLine 45: Same binary download change as above.\\n\\n### 4. `e2e/README.md` — Update Kiro auth docs\\n\\n- Update binary name references\\n- Note that `kiro-cli-chat` (not `kiro-cli`) is required for SIGV4 auth\\n- Update local dev instructions (local users with desktop app can symlink or install separately)\\n\\n## Prerequisites\\n\\n- Infra PR #114 must be merged and applied (creates the IAM role)\\n- `AWS_ROLE_ARN` secret must be set in `entireio/cli` repo settings\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. **Local**: `AMAZON_Q_SIGV4=1 AWS_REGION=us-east-1 AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=<real> AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=<real> kiro-cli-chat chat --no-interactive --agent entire \\\"say hello\\\"` should work\\n2. **CI**: Run isolated E2E test: `e2e-isolated` workflow with agent=kiro, test=TestAttributionOnAgentCommit\\n3. **Unit tests**: `mise run test` (no changes to unit tests needed — this is a config/binary change)\\n\\n## Local dev note\\n\\nDevelopers who have the Kiro desktop app installed get `kiro-cli` (symlink to the app). They need `kiro-cli-chat` separately. The `curl -fsSL https://cli.kiro.dev/install | bash` script may install both — need to verify. If not, local kiro E2E testing requires the direct binary download.\\n\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"d6c8ad70-525c-410b-ba0b-ce08d8dc80ed\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"1013f006-5a3f-4ad0-a4ab-7a352ae10f7b\",\"version\":\"2.1.69\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"toasty-stargazing-mountain\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01PdFQ